modules.description: Provides functions for manipulating and querying a custom tree structure, including node insertion, traversal, and path resolution. Operates on a hierarchical data model represented as labeled nodes with child relationships. Used to efficiently navigate and modify configuration hierarchies in system management tools.

Provides functions to save, load, and manipulate an environment state, including filtering signature items and selectively processing lists. Works with OCaml's internal representation of environments and outphrases. Used to control the visibility of printed output and manage symbol exposure during interactive sessions.
